definitions.definition: A musical art form rooted in West African cultural and musical expression and in the African American blues tradition, with diverse influences over time, commonly characterized by blue notes, syncopation, swing, call and response, polyrhythms and improvisation.
The substance or makeup of a thing.
definitions.example: What is all this jazz lying around?
I'm just going down to the shops and jazz.

definitions.definition: (with positive terms) Something of excellent quality, the genuine article.

definitions.example: You’ve gone and jazzed it now!

definitions.definition: To dance to the tunes of jazz music.
To enliven, brighten up, make more colourful or exciting; excite
To have sex for money, to prostitute oneself.
To move (around/about) in a lively or frivolous manner; to fool around.
